- **Acute:** Sudden pain that needs quick attention
- **Chronic:** Pain lasting 6 months or longer
- **Cyclic:** Pain that comes with your period

**Common Causes:**
- Period cramps (dysmenorrhea)
- Ovarian cysts
- Endometriosis
- Infections
- Fibroids
- Bladder problems
- Bowel problems

**When to See a Doctor:**
- Pain that stops you from doing normal activities
- Pain with fever
- Pain during or after sex
- Unusual vaginal bleeding or discharge
- Pain that keeps getting worse

**What to Expect at Your Visit:**
- Questions about your pain (where, when, how long)
- Physical exam
- Maybe blood tests, urine test, or ultrasound
- Finding the cause helps find the right treatment`,
