*By Duration:*
- Acute: <3 months (may be emergency)
- Chronic: â‰¥6 months

*By Pattern:*
- Cyclic: Related to menstrual cycle
- Non-cyclic: Unrelated to menses
- Intermittent vs. constant

**Differential Diagnosis by System:**

*Gynecologic:*
- Dysmenorrhea (primary or secondary)
- Endometriosis
- Adenomyosis
- Ovarian cysts
- Fibroids
- Pelvic inflammatory disease (PID)
- Adhesions

*Urologic:*
- Interstitial cystitis/bladder pain syndrome
- Urinary tract infection
- Urethral syndrome

*Gastrointestinal:*
- Irritable bowel syndrome (IBS)
- Inflammatory bowel disease
- Constipation
- Diverticular disease

*Musculoskeletal:*
- Pelvic floor dysfunction
- Myofascial pain
- Nerve entrapment

**Evaluation:**
- Detailed history (pain characteristics, associated symptoms)
- Physical exam (abdominal, pelvic, musculoskeletal)
- Labs: Pregnancy test, STI screening, urinalysis
- Imaging: Pelvic ultrasound (transvaginal)
- Laparoscopy if indicated (endometriosis diagnosis)`,
